## Summary
Fix bug where `enable_read_paths` fails when mounting multiple files to the same `/sandbox/` directory.

The original code tried to create the directory with `mkdir` and caught `EEXIST` errors by checking `e.message`. However, Pyodide's `ErrnoError` has no `message` property, causing the second file mount to fail.

## Solution
Instead of catching and filtering mkdir errors, check if the directory exists first using `stat`:

```javascript
try {
  pyodide.FS.stat(cur);
  // Directory exists, continue
} catch {
  // Directory doesn't exist, create it
  pyodide.FS.mkdir(cur);
}
```

This avoids errno handling entirely and is more portable.

## Changes
- `dspy/primitives/runner.js`: Use `stat` to check directory existence before `mkdir`
- `tests/primitives/test_python_interpreter.py`: Add regression test `test_enable_read_paths_multiple_files`

## Test plan
- [x] `pytest tests/primitives/test_python_interpreter.py` - 37 tests pass
- [x] Full test suite - 746 tests pass
- [x] Verified with multiple file mount scenario

