This is trickier than it looks like, because `language` is not a mutable field, and is by nature a class variable instead of pydantic field. 

Dynamic type hint is strongly discouraged: https://github.com/microsoft/pylance-release/issues/5457, so instead of providing something like `dspy.Code(language="java")` I am taking a different approach `dspy.Code["java"]` to achieve the same. See code below for example:

```
import dspy

dspy.configure(lm=dspy.LM("openai/gpt-4o-mini"))


class MySignature(dspy.Signature):
    """Generate code to answer the question."""

    question: str = dspy.InputField(description="The question to answer")
    code: dspy.Code["java"] = dspy.OutputField(description="The code to execute")


predict = dspy.Predict(MySignature)

result = predict(question="Given an array, find if any of the two numbers sum up to 10")
print(result.code)
dspy.inspect_history()
```

