This PR add a new module called CodeAct, which adopts the [CodeAct architecture](https://arxiv.org/abs/2402.01030) to manipulate the Python interpreter with predefined tools. 

```python
from dspy.predict import CodeAct
def factorial(n):
    if n == 1:
        return 1
    return n * factorial(n-1)

act = CodeAct("n->factorial", tools=[factorial])
act(n=5) # 120
```
